<body>

<h1>Google Cloud — Keyless Authentication Setup Guide</h1>
<p><strong>Project:</strong> whatsapp-493623 &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Service Account:</strong> whatsappboot &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Date:</strong> April 2026</p>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Yahan di gayi steps follow karke aap bina JSON key file ke apne local machine se <code>whatsappboot</code> service account ko use kar sakte hain. Ye method Service Account Impersonation with Application Default Credentials (ADC) use karta hai.</p>

<div class="success">
<strong>✅ Google Cloud Console me kya ho chuka hai:</strong><br>
<code>ceo@yhnservices.com</code> ko <strong>Service Account Token Creator</strong> role diya ja chuka hai <code>whatsappboot</code> service account par. Ye ek baar karna tha — ho gaya.
</div>

<h2><span class="step-num">1</span> Google Cloud SDK (gcloud) Install Karo</h2>
<p>Agar gcloud pehle se install nahi hai to niche se install karo:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Windows:</strong> <a href="https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install">https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install</a> se installer download karo</li>
  <li><strong>Mac:</strong> <code>brew install google-cloud-sdk</code></li>
  <li><strong>Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):</strong></li>
</ul>
<div class="code">sudo apt-get install google-cloud-cli</div>
<p>Install hone ke baad terminal me check karo:</p>
<div class="code">gcloud --version</div>

<h2><span class="step-num">2</span> Google Account Se Login Karo</h2>
<p>Terminal / PowerShell / Command Prompt me ye command run karo:</p>
<div class="code">gcloud auth login</div>
<p>Browser automatically khulega. <strong>ceo@yhnservices.com</strong> se login karo aur permission allow karo.</p>

<h2><span class="step-num">3</span> Project Set Karo</h2>
<div class="code">gcloud config set project whatsapp-493623</div>

<h2><span class="step-num">4</span> Application Default Credentials (ADC) Set Karo — WITH Impersonation</h2>
<p>Ye sabse important command hai. Ye command tumhare local machine ke credentials ko <code>whatsappboot</code> service account ke through route karti hai — bina kisi JSON key file ke:</p>
<div class="code">gcloud auth application-default login --impersonate-service-account=whatsappboot@whatsapp-493623.iam.gserviceaccount.com</div>
<p>Command successful hone par terminal me kuch aisa dikhega:</p>
<div class="note">
Credentials saved to file: [C:UsersYourNameAppDataRoaminggcloudapplication_default_credentials.json]<br>
<em>(Ye file automatically manage hoti hai — manually open karne ki zarurat nahi)</em>
</div>

<h2><span class="step-num">5</span> Node.js Setup</h2>
<h3>Package Install Karo</h3>
<p>Apne project folder me ye command run karo:</p>
<div class="code">npm install google-auth-library</div>

<h3>Node.js Code — Test Authentication</h3>
<p>Ek test file banao <code>testAuth.js</code> naam se:</p>
<div class="code">const { GoogleAuth } = require('google-auth-library');<br><br>
async function testAuth() {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;const auth = new GoogleAuth({<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;scopes: ['https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform']<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;});<br><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;const client = await auth.getClient();<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;const token = await client.getAccessToken();<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;console.log('✅ Authentication successful!');<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;console.log('Access Token:', token.token.substring(0, 30) + '...');<br>
}<br><br>
testAuth().catch(console.error);</div>

<p>Run karo:</p>
<div class="code">node testAuth.js</div>

<h3>Apne WhatsApp Bot Me Use Karo</h3>
<p>Agar tum Google APIs (Firestore, Storage, Vertex AI, etc.) use kar rahe ho, to ADC automatically pick ho jaata hai. Example:</p>
<div class="code">const { GoogleAuth } = require('google-auth-library');<br><br>
const auth = new GoogleAuth({<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;scopes: ['https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform']<br>
});<br><br>
// Ye line kaafi hai — baki sab automatically handle hoga<br>
const client = await auth.getClient();</div>

<h2>Summary Table</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Step</th><th>Action</th><th>Status</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Console Setup</td><td>ceo@yhnservices.com ko Token Creator role diya</td><td>✅ Ho chuka hai</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Step 1</td><td>gcloud SDK install karo</td><td>⬜ Tumhari machine par</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Step 2</td><td>gcloud auth login</td><td>⬜ Terminal me run karo</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Step 3</td><td>gcloud config set project whatsapp-493623</td><td>⬜ Terminal me run karo</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Step 4</td><td>gcloud auth application-default login --impersonate-service-account=...</td><td>⬜ Terminal me run karo</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Step 5</td><td>npm install google-auth-library + code update</td><td>⬜ Node.js project me</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="note">
<strong>⚠️ Important Notes:</strong><br>
• JSON key file ki zarurat nahi — koi file share mat karna, koi secret store mat karna.<br>
• Agar machine change karo to Step 2, 3, 4 dobara run karni hongi.<br>
• Token automatically refresh hota rehta hai — expire hone ki chinta nahi.<br>
• Agar koi error aaye to <code>gcloud auth application-default print-access-token</code> se debug karo.
</div>

<p style="margin-top:30px; color:#888; font-size:9pt;">Generated for: Whatsapp Project (whatsapp-493623) | Service Account: whatsappboot@whatsapp-493623.iam.gserviceaccount.com</p>

</body>
